<b>Diabetic Retinopathy (DR)</b> is a co: Diabetic Retinopathy (DR) is a common complication of diabetes, caused by high blood sugar levels damaging the retina. DR may cause blurring of central vision when reading or driving, loss of the ability to see colour, and/or distortion of images.
<b>Glaucoma</b> is a condition where the: Glaucoma is a condition where the optic nerve which connects the eye to the brain becomes damaged due to build-up of pressure in the eye. Glaucoma can have symptoms such as blurred vision, or seeing rainbow-coloured circles around bright lights.
<b>Age-related Macular Degeneration (AMD: Age-related Macular Degeneration (AMD) is an age-related deterioration of the vision focal point in your eye. AMD can interfere with daily activities such as driving, reading, writing etc.
How can you reduce this risk?: How can you reduce this risk?
&#9632; Know your family eye history<br>:
■ Know your family eye history
■ Exercise regularly
■ Eat a healthy, balanced diet – in particular, cut down on salt, fat and sugar
■ Monitor your blood sugar levels, blood pressure and cholesterol levels regularly to keep them under control
■ Wear sunglasses when going out if you have higher risk factors
